00:28:24,205 --> 00:28:25,306
(ENGINE TURNS OFF)

527
00:28:27,249 --> 00:28:28,642
(ENGINE STARTS)

528
00:28:32,463 --> 00:28:33,963
What are you doing here?

529
00:28:33,964 --> 00:28:35,048
- Get away from that car.
- Stop.

530
00:28:35,049 --> 00:28:36,567
Look, it's working.

531
00:28:36,634 --> 00:28:39,302
It was the old carburetor.
It was shot.

532
00:28:39,303 --> 00:28:40,804
I had the right one
laying around the shop,

533
00:28:40,805 --> 00:28:43,431
so I thought you might
wanna hear her run again.

534
00:28:43,432 --> 00:28:44,825
(ENGINE SPUTTERING)

535
00:28:47,436 --> 00:28:49,580
That's amazing! What did you do?

536
00:28:49,647 --> 00:28:51,832
- It's no big deal.
- JADE: Thank you.

537
00:28:51,941 --> 00:28:53,650
I never thought I'd
hear that sound again.

538
00:28:53,651 --> 00:28:55,419
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

539
00:29:01,325 --> 00:29:04,327
Look, Jade told me how much
this car meant to you.

540
00:29:04,328 --> 00:29:06,496
And I tried to rack my brain
around something I could do,

541
00:29:06,497 --> 00:29:11,352
seeing as, you know, we got off on
the wrong foot the other night.

543
00:29:11,377 --> 00:29:12,895
The other night.

544
00:29:14,171 --> 00:29:15,564
(CHUCKLING)

545
00:29:16,132 --> 00:29:18,400
When you emerged from a
closet with my daughter.

546
00:29:18,426 --> 00:29:20,569
Dad, he did this for us.

547
00:29:21,345 --> 00:29:23,555
ANNE:
It's a very kind gesture, David.

548
00:29:23,556 --> 00:29:26,325
Would you maybe, um,
join us for dinner?

549
00:29:26,350 --> 00:29:27,934
I wasn't looking for an invite.

550
00:29:27,935 --> 00:29:29,245
I should go home and shower.

551
00:29:29,395 --> 00:29:31,455
You could wash up here.
I have to get changed.

552
00:29:31,522 --> 00:29:32,647
I don't wanna intrude.

553
00:29:32,648 --> 00:29:34,416
No, you wouldn't be
intruding, honestly.

554
00:29:34,608 --> 00:29:35,960
Dad, please.

555
00:29:37,361 --> 00:29:40,089
Yeah, okay. Sure, sure, yeah.

556
00:29:40,156 --> 00:29:41,799
- ANNE: Great.
- Come on.

557
00:29:42,950 --> 00:29:44,743
You might not know this, David,

558
00:29:44,744 --> 00:29:49,330
but, uh, Jade is following
in her father's footsteps,

559
00:29:49,331 --> 00:29:50,874
enrolling pre-med in the fall.

560
00:29:50,875 --> 00:29:55,646
And since I'm kind of hoping
for a specialty in cardiology,

561
00:29:56,756 --> 00:30:00,985
I just thought there was no better way to
celebrate than with a family heirloom.

562
00:30:01,177 --> 00:30:03,612
No more gifts, Dad.
You've gotten me enough.

563
00:30:03,679 --> 00:30:05,489
It was your grandfather's.

564
00:30:05,723 --> 00:30:07,241
It was mine.

565
00:30:07,391 --> 00:30:10,828
And it was gonna be Chris',
and now it's yours.

566
00:30:11,520 --> 00:30:12,663
(JADE GASPS)

567
00:30:12,897 --> 00:30:15,916
Oh, it's too much. Thank you.

568
00:30:16,359 --> 00:30:19,003
Well, I think pre-med
at Brown earns it.

569
00:30:20,237 --> 00:30:22,798
Not to mention your internship
with Dr. Fitzgerald.

570
00:30:22,865 --> 00:30:25,468
Internship? You never
mentioned that.

571
00:30:25,785 --> 00:30:27,118
It's not a big deal, that's why.

572
00:30:27,119 --> 00:30:28,203
Very big deal.

573
00:30:28,204 --> 00:30:30,497
I mean, she'll be leaving and
spending, I don't know, most of...

574
00:30:30,498 --> 00:30:32,874
Um, I, uh, had to
declare my major, too.

575
00:30:32,875 --> 00:30:37,128
It's not as fancy as Jade's, but I
had to major in something, so...

576
00:30:37,129 --> 00:30:38,314
Communications.

577
00:30:38,923 --> 00:30:40,524
Communications.

578
00:30:41,133 --> 00:30:42,509
Always wondered what that meant.

579
00:30:42,510 --> 00:30:44,737
It's the study of
how we communicate.

580
00:30:44,970 --> 00:30:49,366
Well, you know, you can always change
it later if it doesn't make sense.

581
00:30:50,226 --> 00:30:52,870
All right, David. Your turn.

582
00:30:52,937 --> 00:30:54,437
Ah, here it comes, the inquisition.

583
00:30:54,438 --> 00:30:55,915
(CHUCKLES)

584
00:30:55,940 --> 00:30:58,334
It's okay. If I can
pass, you can pass.

585
00:30:58,401 --> 00:31:01,712
Keith, did she pass? He still
doesn't call you his girlfriend.

586
00:31:01,779 --> 00:31:05,448
Okay, David, look, we know your
act of generosity with the car

587
00:31:05,449 --> 00:31:08,410
wasn't really about anything
other than my daughter, so...

588
00:31:08,411 --> 00:31:09,786
(LAUGHING)

589
00:31:09,787 --> 00:31:11,705
I'd just love to know a
little more about you,

590
00:31:11,706 --> 00:31:13,456
other than the fact you
can fix an old car.

591
00:31:13,457 --> 00:31:15,726
I'm sure that's not your
most noteworthy quality.

592
00:31:15,793 --> 00:31:16,977
I mean, it might be.

593
00:31:17,044 --> 00:31:19,105
What about your future plans?
Where are you going to college?

594
00:31:19,130 --> 00:31:21,107
Uh, I'm not going to college.

595
00:31:21,799 --> 00:31:23,067
- Oh.
- Mmm.

596
00:31:23,801 --> 00:31:24,902
Don't feel you need it?

597
00:31:25,302 --> 00:31:28,072
No, I'm not saying that.
I took my SATs.

598
00:31:28,806 --> 00:31:29,889
Well, I mean...

599
00:31:29,890 --> 00:31:31,558
No, I wouldn't let
that discourage you.

600
00:31:31,559 --> 00:31:33,143
I mean, not everybody tests well.

601
00:31:33,144 --> 00:31:34,394
Ah, I got a 2090.

602
00:31:34,395 --> 00:31:36,521
(LAUGHING) Well done.

603
00:31:36,522 --> 00:31:37,856
SABINE:
That's an amazing score, David.

604
00:31:37,857 --> 00:31:39,441
You could get into
UGA with that score.

605
00:31:39,442 --> 00:31:42,419
Maybe. But I like working
in my dad's shop.

606
00:31:42,737 --> 00:31:43,921
And so does he.

607
00:31:43,946 --> 00:31:45,613
And there's nothing
wrong with that.

608
00:31:45,614 --> 00:31:46,966
Yeah, I don't need much.

609
00:31:47,783 --> 00:31:50,761
Warm bed, clean socks,
milk in the fridge.

610
00:31:50,828 --> 00:31:53,305
- A nice girl to come home to.
- (HUGH CHUCKLES)

611
00:31:53,372 --> 00:31:55,165
Modern-day romantic. I see.

612
00:31:55,166 --> 00:31:58,436
- Can I just give you a piece of advice?
- Oh, no, Hugh.

613
00:31:58,502 --> 00:32:02,005
Speaking as someone who's been
married for over two decades.

614
00:32:02,006 --> 00:32:06,986
I mean, love is wonderful,
but it's not all you need.

616
00:32:08,179 --> 00:32:10,614
You also need things
like life insurance

617
00:32:10,639 --> 00:32:14,326
and PPOs and unromantic
things, like mortgages.

618
00:32:14,852 --> 00:32:16,162
I get that.

619
00:32:17,021 --> 00:32:18,688
I mean, I'm sure
I'll have all those things one day,

620
00:32:18,689 --> 00:32:21,149
but I do think
that love comes first, you know?

621
00:32:21,150 --> 00:32:23,411
At the end of the day,
what's more important than that?

622
00:32:23,486 --> 00:32:24,652
KEITH: Oxygen.

623
00:32:24,653 --> 00:32:26,071
Shut up, Keith.

624
00:32:26,072 --> 00:32:27,298
(CHUCKLES)

625
00:32:27,698 --> 00:32:30,509
You know, I've seen it firsthand.

626
00:32:32,244 --> 00:32:34,638
I know what it's like
when it's there,

627
00:32:37,708 --> 00:32:39,643
and I know what it's
like when it's not.

628
00:32:41,003 --> 00:32:42,605
So you've been in love before.

629
00:32:42,880 --> 00:32:44,732
No, no. (CHUCKLES)

630
00:32:45,383 --> 00:32:46,716
But my parents were.

631
00:32:46,717 --> 00:32:49,719
They met when they were in high
school, and it made sense.

632
00:32:49,720 --> 00:32:52,656
That's what I wanna find.
True love.

633
00:32:52,723 --> 00:32:55,993
The kind that you fight for,
that you always put first.

634
00:32:56,435 --> 00:33:00,664
That makes you wanna
be good and do better.

635
00:33:02,400 --> 00:33:04,376
And not just with any girl.

636
00:33:04,777 --> 00:33:06,212
But "the" girl.

637
00:33:07,780 --> 00:33:09,673
And when I find that,

638
00:33:10,199 --> 00:33:11,967
that's all I need.

639
00:33:13,536 --> 00:33:14,845
HUGH: Homeless and in love.

640
00:33:16,956 --> 00:33:18,557
Sounds great.

641
00:33:19,166 --> 00:33:21,376
Maybe I should have said
I was going to college.

642
00:33:21,377 --> 00:33:22,978
- (CHUCKLING)
- Yeah.

643
00:33:23,129 --> 00:33:25,714
I hope that you find that, David.

644
00:33:25,715 --> 00:33:28,776
Thank you.
I mean, you and Hugh did.

645
00:33:28,843 --> 00:33:31,195
Yeah. Yeah. Oh.

646
00:33:31,470 --> 00:33:32,637
To love.

647
00:33:32,638 --> 00:33:33,989
(ANNE CHUCKLES)

648
00:33:34,807 --> 00:33:36,242
HUGH: Yes, to love.

649
00:33:36,726 --> 00:33:37,767
- To love.
- DAVID: To love.

650
00:33:37,768 --> 00:33:39,370
- JADE: To love.
- (GLASSES CLINKING)

651
00:33:45,317 --> 00:33:47,152
I found what you said inspiring.

652
00:33:47,153 --> 00:33:50,881
And inspiration has been in
short supply these days.

653
00:33:51,657 --> 00:33:53,408
Uh, Jade tells me you're a writer.

654
00:33:53,409 --> 00:33:54,951
Oh, I was a writer.

655
00:33:54,952 --> 00:33:59,622
I wrote one book, but then, um,
life got in the way, so...

656
00:33:59,623 --> 00:34:01,791
I've never met an author before.

657
00:34:01,792 --> 00:34:04,711
If I got one of your books,
would you sign it for me?

658
00:34:04,712 --> 00:34:06,522
(CHUCKLING)

659
00:34:07,131 --> 00:34:08,691
Sure.

660
00:34:09,633 --> 00:34:11,902
- Thanks. (CHUCKLES)
- Thank you.

661
00:34:14,096 --> 00:34:15,531
Good night, David.

662
00:34:15,598 --> 00:34:17,032
Thank you, sir.

663
00:34:25,024 --> 00:34:27,293
- Good night.
- ANNE: Good night.

664
00:34:31,781 --> 00:34:33,174
(CHUCKLES)

665
00:34:38,621 --> 00:34:39,930
JADE: David!

666
00:34:43,751 --> 00:34:45,186
(CHUCKLES)

667
00:34:54,512 --> 00:34:57,806
She's leaving in two weeks. What
do you think he wants with her?

668
00:34:57,807 --> 00:34:59,533
He's falling in love with her.

669
00:35:00,685 --> 00:35:02,143
Well, she's not ready for that.

670
00:35:02,144 --> 00:35:06,123
(CHUCKLES) Of course she is.
She's 17. It's her time.

671
00:35:06,148 --> 00:35:08,125
She's never expressed any interest.

672
00:35:09,402 --> 00:35:11,128
Oh, you haven't exactly let her.

673
00:35:12,154 --> 00:35:13,196
So what should I do?

674
00:35:13,197 --> 00:35:16,091
I should just encourage her to fall
in love and have her heart broken?

675
00:35:16,158 --> 00:35:17,867
Yes, you should.

676
00:35:17,868 --> 00:35:19,929
I think she'd be great at it.

677
00:35:20,162 --> 00:35:21,347
I was.

678
00:35:25,835 --> 00:35:27,561
Don't make this about us.

679
00:36:11,589 --> 00:36:12,672
(FLOOR CREAKS)

680
00:36:12,673 --> 00:36:13,858
Careful.

681
00:36:16,594 --> 00:36:17,820
(SHUSHING)

682
00:36:31,776 --> 00:36:33,294
You're shaking.

683
00:36:33,694 --> 00:36:35,421
Good shaking.

684
00:36:44,830 --> 00:36:46,599
We don't have to do this.

685
00:36:48,334 --> 00:36:50,311
As much as I want to,

686
00:36:51,545 --> 00:36:53,397
I can wait.

687
00:36:54,840 --> 00:36:56,901
I don't wanna wait.

688
00:36:58,636 --> 00:37:00,738
I wanna feel this with you.

689
00:37:53,524 --> 00:37:54,625
Fast.

690
00:38:00,448 --> 00:38:01,531
(CELL PHONE BEEPS)

691
00:38:01,532 --> 00:38:02,800
Who are you texting?

692
00:38:02,867 --> 00:38:05,136
That's unbelievably rude,
after what we just did.

693
00:38:05,244 --> 00:38:06,870
(CELL PHONE CHIMES)

694
00:38:06,871 --> 00:38:08,097
(CHUCKLES)

695
00:38:12,209 --> 00:38:13,769
(JADE CHUCKLES)

696
00:38:19,967 --> 00:38:21,193
So...

697
00:38:28,768 --> 00:38:30,661
Don't you have to be at
your dad's shop soon?

698
00:38:31,145 --> 00:38:33,664
I should probably go
before everyone wakes up.

699
00:38:44,075 --> 00:38:45,426
(CHUCKLES)

700
00:38:46,619 --> 00:38:49,746
It's mine now.
Your first present to me.

701
00:38:49,747 --> 00:38:51,182
(CHUCKLES)

702
00:38:58,506 --> 00:38:59,648
I remember him.

703
00:39:00,925 --> 00:39:02,258
You do?

704
00:39:02,259 --> 00:39:03,527
Yeah.

705
00:39:04,553 --> 00:39:07,323
We were in seventh grade
when he was a senior.

706
00:39:07,973 --> 00:39:09,241
(CHUCKLES)

707
00:39:09,433 --> 00:39:12,703
He was good. I remember that.

708
00:39:14,021 --> 00:39:15,664
He was good.

709
00:39:18,859 --> 00:39:20,586
What's it like to have lost him?

710
00:39:21,904 --> 00:39:24,715
My dad, he saved us all.

711
00:39:25,991 --> 00:39:29,428
After Chris got cancer, he stopped
working to take care of him.

712
00:39:29,578 --> 00:39:31,454
We wouldn't have got
through it without him.

713
00:39:31,455 --> 00:39:34,391
And we're doing so
much better, really.

714
00:39:35,626 --> 00:39:37,377
I'm lucky that way.

715
00:39:37,378 --> 00:39:40,940
Some families never heal,
and we're doing so well.

716
00:39:44,218 --> 00:39:46,612
It's okay if none of that is true.

717
00:39:48,389 --> 00:39:49,556
But it is.

718
00:39:49,557 --> 00:39:52,576
I know. I'm just saying
it's okay if it's not.

719
00:39:57,231 --> 00:39:58,898
(SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE)

720
00:39:58,899 --> 00:40:00,835
JADE: Enlarged ventricles.

721
00:40:01,986 --> 00:40:03,278
Cardiomegaly.

722
00:40:03,279 --> 00:40:04,755
Course of treatment?

723
00:40:05,156 --> 00:40:08,634
Check the patient's kidneys.
Could be in renal failure.

724
00:40:09,994 --> 00:40:11,095
That's good.

725
00:40:11,328 --> 00:40:12,662
So you can stay for
the next surgery.

726
00:40:12,663 --> 00:40:15,457
I've got an angioplasty
starting at 2:00.

727
00:40:15,458 --> 00:40:18,436
Oh. I actually have plans.

728
00:40:19,295 --> 00:40:20,729
I'm sorry.

729
00:40:23,007 --> 00:40:26,509
Does he know that this thing is gonna
be ending in a couple of weeks?

731
00:40:26,510 --> 00:40:30,531
'Cause the kid at dinner last
night didn't really seem to know.

732
00:40:31,849 --> 00:40:33,284
Of course he does.

733
00:40:35,853 --> 00:40:37,788
I thought we had the summer.

734
00:40:39,231 --> 00:40:42,793
I know, but it's too competitive.
I can't turn it down.

735
00:40:46,947 --> 00:40:48,632
Say something.

736
00:40:55,122 --> 00:40:56,223
I don't care.

737
00:40:58,459 --> 00:40:59,727
I don't.

738
00:40:59,919 --> 00:41:04,482
I don't care if we have 10
days, or one week or one day.

739
00:41:05,383 --> 00:41:07,067
I want you to spend it with me.

740
00:41:07,468 --> 00:41:08,569
(CHUCKLES)

741
00:41:09,387 --> 00:41:10,571
And if I do?

742
00:41:11,263 --> 00:41:12,430
(INHALES)

743
00:41:12,431 --> 00:41:13,991
I promise you

744
00:41:15,267 --> 00:41:17,703
they'll be the best
10 days of your life.

745
00:41:25,861 --> 00:41:26,962
(CHUCKLES)

746
00:42:21,459 --> 00:42:23,394
(GIRLS SCREAMING)

747
00:42:24,670 --> 00:42:25,771
Have a snack!

748
00:42:28,049 --> 00:42:29,525
(SCREAMING)

749
00:42:33,804 --> 00:42:35,555
There's two more days.

750
00:42:35,556 --> 00:42:37,908
You better have something
amazing planned.

751
00:42:39,810 --> 00:42:40,911
Maybe.

752
00:42:48,652 --> 00:42:50,129
(CROWD CHEERING)

753
00:42:51,989 --> 00:42:53,090
(LAUGHING)

754
00:43:02,124 --> 00:43:03,642
(CHEERING)

755
00:43:30,611 --> 00:43:32,171
I love you, too.

756
00:44:11,068 --> 00:44:12,294
(BEEPING)

757
00:44:33,924 --> 00:44:36,485
I don't wanna leave.
Tell me to stay.

758
00:44:37,595 --> 00:44:38,946
I want to, but...

759
00:44:39,513 --> 00:44:41,598
I don't care about the internship.

760
00:44:41,599 --> 00:44:43,179
I want to be with
you for the summer.

761
00:44:43,267 --> 00:44:45,911
- You mean that?
- Yeah.

762
00:44:52,026 --> 00:44:53,127
- Then stay.
- (CHUCKLES)

763
00:44:56,030 --> 00:44:57,256
Stay.

764
00:44:57,656 --> 00:44:58,757
(MUFFLED SCREAMING)

765
00:44:58,783 --> 00:45:00,384
- Stay.
- (CHUCKLING)

766
00:45:01,994 --> 00:45:03,095
(DOOR OPENS)

767
00:45:03,579 --> 00:45:04,680
(DOOR CLOSES)

