00:45:20,304 --> 00:45:21,489
Oh, you're home late.

771
00:45:21,597 --> 00:45:22,806
I'm tired, Dad. Please.

772
00:45:22,807 --> 00:45:26,118
Can I just ask you why
you're unpacking?

773
00:45:26,185 --> 00:45:28,204
I called Dr. Fitzgerald.

774
00:45:28,437 --> 00:45:30,080
I'm not taking the internship.

775
00:45:30,773 --> 00:45:32,082
(EXHALES)

776
00:45:32,733 --> 00:45:34,084
(SIGHS)

777
00:45:34,652 --> 00:45:36,128
So David put you up to this?

778
00:45:36,153 --> 00:45:37,987
No. It was my decision.

779
00:45:37,988 --> 00:45:41,783
The internship is your
ticket into medical school.

780
00:45:41,784 --> 00:45:44,411
It's not something you
can just walk away from.

781
00:45:44,412 --> 00:45:46,705
I know. But I'm an
incoming freshman

782
00:45:46,706 --> 00:45:48,498
and I have four years
to find another ticket.

783
00:45:48,499 --> 00:45:51,167
I went out on a limb with
Dr. Fitzgerald for you.

784
00:45:51,168 --> 00:45:54,271
I'm sorry. But I'm allowed
to change my mind.

785
00:45:58,592 --> 00:46:02,196
So, this has nothing
to do with David?

786
00:46:03,347 --> 00:46:04,556
No.

787
00:46:04,557 --> 00:46:06,200
Then what's going on?

788
00:46:06,434 --> 00:46:09,703
We used to talk.
This doesn't make sense.

789
00:46:11,647 --> 00:46:12,790
(SIGHS DEEPLY)

790
00:46:15,568 --> 00:46:17,670
Maybe I do want more
time with David.

791
00:46:18,112 --> 00:46:19,421
Honey.

792
00:46:19,488 --> 00:46:22,007
- You must have felt this way once.
- (SIGHS)

793
00:46:22,074 --> 00:46:23,425
With Mom?

794
00:46:23,868 --> 00:46:28,121
Yeah. But we hadn't just
graduated high school.

795
00:46:28,122 --> 00:46:31,100
I was through medical school by the
time your mom and I got serious.

796
00:46:31,167 --> 00:46:32,625
That's not where I am.

797
00:46:32,626 --> 00:46:35,062
- Well...
- I'm here now,

798
00:46:35,921 --> 00:46:38,482
and I've never felt
this way about anyone.

799
00:46:39,925 --> 00:46:42,862
I thought about it,
and I dreamt about it.

800
00:46:43,346 --> 00:46:45,656
I just never thought it
would actually happen.

801
00:46:45,723 --> 00:46:47,700
And now that it has,

802
00:46:48,601 --> 00:46:49,910
I need more time.

803
00:46:50,728 --> 00:46:51,996
(SIGHS)

804
00:46:54,398 --> 00:46:56,816
You know, of all the reasons

805
00:46:56,817 --> 00:46:59,962
to sacrifice something that
you've worked so hard for,

806
00:47:01,072 --> 00:47:02,590
a boy.

807
00:47:03,115 --> 00:47:05,009
It's very unlike you.

808
00:47:07,995 --> 00:47:09,346
(DOOR CLOSES)

809
00:47:19,131 --> 00:47:20,941
(CAR DOOR CLOSES)

810
00:47:31,143 --> 00:47:32,703
What's going on?

811
00:47:32,812 --> 00:47:34,229
Ah, we're going to the lake house.

812
00:47:34,230 --> 00:47:36,481
Get dressed. Your bathing
suit's still in the dryer.

813
00:47:36,482 --> 00:47:37,565
For the weekend?

814
00:47:37,566 --> 00:47:38,650
- Hi, Jade.
- Hi.

815
00:47:38,651 --> 00:47:39,734
Um, I don't know.

816
00:47:39,735 --> 00:47:41,361
Uh, pack enough for
a couple of weeks.

817
00:47:41,362 --> 00:47:43,589
Your sentence begins now.

818
00:47:43,656 --> 00:47:44,948
Heard about the internship.

819
00:47:44,949 --> 00:47:47,089
Nice to know I'm not the
only one disappointing Dad.

820
00:47:49,203 --> 00:47:51,162
You didn't tell me we were
going to the lake house.

821
00:47:51,163 --> 00:47:52,330
Well, I think we need it, Jade.

822
00:47:52,331 --> 00:47:54,290
I think we need to spend
time together as a family.

823
00:47:54,291 --> 00:47:55,417
I think we're drifting.

824
00:47:55,418 --> 00:47:57,752
I don't wanna go! You know that!

825
00:47:57,753 --> 00:47:59,295
I can't leave David now!

826
00:47:59,296 --> 00:48:01,506
You're going to the lake
house with your family,

827
00:48:01,507 --> 00:48:03,647
and I'm not gonna hear any
more complaints about it.

828
00:48:04,927 --> 00:48:06,320
Get your stuff.

829
00:48:12,768 --> 00:48:14,644
Hey, man. Where you been?

830
00:48:14,645 --> 00:48:16,021
(CHUCKLES)

831
00:48:16,022 --> 00:48:18,231
I was with Jade. Why, you miss me?

832
00:48:18,232 --> 00:48:20,900
Sure, yeah. Most nights I've
been crying myself to sleep.

833
00:48:20,901 --> 00:48:22,002
(CHUCKLES)

834
00:48:25,948 --> 00:48:27,091
UGA?

835
00:48:27,324 --> 00:48:28,676
(ENGINE SPUTTERING)

836
00:48:28,909 --> 00:48:30,928
I didn't know you were thinking
about going to college.

837
00:48:31,037 --> 00:48:33,097
Uh, I wasn't until recently.

838
00:48:35,958 --> 00:48:38,394
College boy.
Yeah, I could see that.

839
00:48:39,170 --> 00:48:40,211
Think you got a shot?

840
00:48:40,212 --> 00:48:43,298
Jade's mom's gonna write a
letter of recommendation.

841
00:48:43,299 --> 00:48:45,860
Plus, she used to work there, so...

842
00:48:50,181 --> 00:48:51,615
I'm still gonna work in the shop.

843
00:48:51,849 --> 00:48:53,183
Oh...

844
00:48:53,184 --> 00:48:54,726
I like the idea.

845
00:48:54,727 --> 00:48:57,496
I was wondering how I'd
afford early retirement.

846
00:49:00,649 --> 00:49:01,834
(CAR DOOR CLOSES)

847
00:49:08,699 --> 00:49:11,635
ANNE: Wait, wait a minute.
I have the key.

848
00:49:16,874 --> 00:49:18,249
Anyone wanna take a swim?

849
00:49:18,250 --> 00:49:20,877
No, we're starving. I'm gonna
take Sabine into town.

850
00:49:20,878 --> 00:49:22,045
Can we bring something back?

851
00:49:22,046 --> 00:49:23,463
HUGH: No, I'm fine.

852
00:49:23,464 --> 00:49:26,650
- Sense of humor? Jagermeister, maybe?
- (CHUCKLING)

853
00:49:27,718 --> 00:49:28,819
Do you want anything?

854
00:49:29,428 --> 00:49:30,571
No.

855
00:49:38,437 --> 00:49:40,164
I'll take a swim with you.

856
00:49:42,733 --> 00:49:43,959
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

857
00:49:44,068 --> 00:49:45,169
JADE: I'll get it.

858
00:49:49,615 --> 00:49:51,842
- Hey.
- Thank God you're here.

859
00:49:54,328 --> 00:49:55,513
- Hey.
- ANNE: Hey.

860
00:49:56,330 --> 00:49:57,789
- These are for you.
- Thank you.

861
00:49:57,790 --> 00:49:59,416
Thank you so much for having me.

862
00:49:59,417 --> 00:50:01,126
You have a beautiful house.

863
00:50:01,127 --> 00:50:03,587
- JADE: Amazing, isn't it?
- What are you doing here, David?

864
00:50:04,088 --> 00:50:05,523
Uh, Jade invited me.

865
00:50:06,549 --> 00:50:09,342
Keith invited Sabine. I don't
see what the problem is.

866
00:50:09,343 --> 00:50:12,721
The problem is this is
meant to be a family trip.

867
00:50:12,722 --> 00:50:16,075
I'm sorry, but inviting David
was never part of the plan.

868
00:50:17,518 --> 00:50:18,619
(SIGHS)

869
00:50:18,978 --> 00:50:20,061
He didn't know?

870
00:50:20,062 --> 00:50:21,146
It's fine, David.

871
00:50:21,147 --> 00:50:23,207
- The more the merrier.
- HUGH: No, it's not fine.

872
00:50:23,232 --> 00:50:24,542
ANNE: Hugh, please.

873
00:50:24,608 --> 00:50:26,693
Well, he's here now, and I
don't want him to leave.

874
00:50:26,694 --> 00:50:27,875
Well, that's not up to you.

875
00:50:28,487 --> 00:50:29,880
Actually, it is.

876
00:50:30,448 --> 00:50:32,716
He's my guest and he's staying.

877
00:50:39,081 --> 00:50:40,165
(EXHALES)

878
00:50:40,166 --> 00:50:41,892
Jade just became a woman.

879
00:50:42,668 --> 00:50:44,336
You didn't tell your dad?

880
00:50:44,337 --> 00:50:45,545
He's never gonna forgive me now.

881
00:50:45,546 --> 00:50:46,921
He'll get over it, I promise.

882
00:50:46,922 --> 00:50:49,549
Now you have the perfect chance to
show him how wonderful you are.

883
00:50:49,550 --> 00:50:50,818
What are you doing?

884
00:50:52,428 --> 00:50:53,737
Come on. (CHUCKLES)

885
00:50:55,014 --> 00:50:56,139
Come on!

886
00:50:56,140 --> 00:50:57,223
Really?

887
00:50:57,224 --> 00:50:58,617
Take it off.

888
00:51:00,102 --> 00:51:01,412
Come on.

889
00:51:02,188 --> 00:51:03,414
Hurry up!

890
00:51:09,487 --> 00:51:11,255
- (SCREAMING)
- Whoo!

891
00:51:11,906 --> 00:51:13,757
I don't even recognize her.

892
00:51:14,617 --> 00:51:18,804
And you know, she would never
act this way before him.

893
00:51:19,121 --> 00:51:21,307
I think she's right on track.

894
00:51:22,958 --> 00:51:24,977
Giving up the internship
is right on track?

895
00:51:25,044 --> 00:51:28,505
Didn't it ever worry you that
she wasn't out in the world

896
00:51:28,506 --> 00:51:30,107
experiencing life?

897
00:51:30,800 --> 00:51:35,488
She spent the past two years either by
our sides or with her nose in a book.

898
00:51:35,888 --> 00:51:37,740
She deserves to have
fun this summer.

899
00:51:37,807 --> 00:51:39,784
Well, she was mourning her brother.

900
00:51:39,975 --> 00:51:42,536
You can't expect her to go to a
slumber party every weekend.

901
00:51:42,603 --> 00:51:45,122
I know very well who
she was mourning.

902
00:51:46,190 --> 00:51:49,418
She just lost her teenage years
and now she's finding them.

903
00:51:49,652 --> 00:51:51,152
HUGH: Yeah, with a total stranger.

904
00:51:51,153 --> 00:51:52,487
We don't know anything about him.

905
00:51:52,488 --> 00:51:53,589
(SIGHS)

906
00:51:54,073 --> 00:51:57,218
She is falling in love, Hugh.

907
00:51:57,284 --> 00:52:01,055
When did you last see her
this happy? Hmm? When?

908
00:52:02,707 --> 00:52:04,058
I don't know.

909
00:52:05,626 --> 00:52:06,876
That's something you wanna end?

910
00:52:06,877 --> 00:52:08,062
(SIGHS DEEPLY)

911
00:52:10,464 --> 00:52:12,775
HUGH: (STAMMERING)
I gotta say something.

912
00:52:13,134 --> 00:52:15,152
I need to apologize to David.

913
00:52:16,262 --> 00:52:20,991
I might have overreacted
slightly when you arrived,

914
00:52:24,020 --> 00:52:25,121
and, uh, I'm sorry.

915
00:52:25,479 --> 00:52:26,914
Thank you.

916
00:52:28,482 --> 00:52:32,002
So, maybe, clean slate?

917
00:52:32,236 --> 00:52:34,296
Yeah, that would be great.

918
00:52:34,739 --> 00:52:35,864
(ALL CHUCKLING)

919
00:52:35,865 --> 00:52:37,591
Nice. Cheers.

920
00:52:37,742 --> 00:52:38,843
Thanks, Dad.

921
00:52:38,909 --> 00:52:41,554
ANNE: Aw, that was beautiful.

922
00:52:41,954 --> 00:52:43,038
Berries, anyone?

923
00:52:43,039 --> 00:52:44,807
Mom, David finished your book.

924
00:52:45,332 --> 00:52:47,292
- I loved it.
- She's an amazing writer, right?

925
00:52:47,293 --> 00:52:49,252
Yeah, maybe you'll feel
ready to write again soon.

926
00:52:49,253 --> 00:52:50,754
- You should.
- Yeah, maybe.

927
00:52:50,755 --> 00:52:52,380
You reminded me how
much I love reading

928
00:52:52,381 --> 00:52:55,025
and how much more I need to do.

929
00:52:55,259 --> 00:52:57,177
Well, you'll have more
books than you know

930
00:52:57,178 --> 00:52:59,095
what to do with at the
University of Georgia.

931
00:52:59,096 --> 00:53:00,263
You think I have a chance?

932
00:53:00,264 --> 00:53:02,015
Of course. With your SATs?

933
00:53:02,016 --> 00:53:04,034
And Mom's letter.
They love her there.

934
00:53:04,060 --> 00:53:06,036
So, you're applying to college?

935
00:53:06,729 --> 00:53:08,456
Yeah. Yeah.

936
00:53:08,522 --> 00:53:10,523
Second semester. Hopefully.

937
00:53:10,524 --> 00:53:11,959
DAWN: Knock, knock.

938
00:53:12,026 --> 00:53:13,252
- Hi.
- ANNE: Oh.

939
00:53:14,028 --> 00:53:15,278
I didn't know Dawn was here.

940
00:53:15,279 --> 00:53:16,464
No, neither did I.

941
00:53:16,906 --> 00:53:18,299
- HUGH: Hey.
- Hi.

942
00:53:18,366 --> 00:53:19,717
- Hi.
- HUGH: How are you?

943
00:53:20,409 --> 00:53:22,243
It's a work colleague of Hugh's.

944
00:53:22,244 --> 00:53:23,637
I think I met her at the party.

945
00:53:24,914 --> 00:53:26,664
You know what?
I'm feeling inspired.

946
00:53:26,665 --> 00:53:30,394
I'm gonna go inside and write
that letter. (CHUCKLES)

947
00:53:31,087 --> 00:53:32,396
Hey.

948
00:53:32,755 --> 00:53:33,880
- Hey.
- Hey.

949
00:53:33,881 --> 00:53:35,941
- Do you wanna do something fun?
- Yeah.

950
00:53:36,926 --> 00:53:38,569
(SCREAMING)

951
00:53:41,806 --> 00:53:43,115
Whoo!

952
00:53:48,104 --> 00:53:49,312
Yeah!

953
00:53:49,313 --> 00:53:50,730
ALL: One, two, three!

954
00:53:50,731 --> 00:53:51,999
(ALL CHEERING)

955
00:53:54,777 --> 00:53:56,003
(JADE CHUCKLES)

956
00:54:02,451 --> 00:54:04,178
We need more sparklers!

957
00:54:05,830 --> 00:54:07,556
- What?
- We need more sparklers.

958
00:54:07,581 --> 00:54:08,999
Okay. I'll go get some.

959
00:54:09,000 --> 00:54:11,268
KEITH:
Yeah. Top shelf in the garage.

960
00:54:28,310 --> 00:54:29,477
(DOOR LOCK CLICKS)

961
00:54:29,478 --> 00:54:30,663
What?

962
00:54:31,772 --> 00:54:33,582
- What?
- Did you hear something?

963
00:54:34,650 --> 00:54:36,276
- JADE: David, did you find them?
- What?

964
00:54:36,277 --> 00:54:38,129
- Uh, no, we're all out.
- We can't be.

965
00:54:38,195 --> 00:54:39,964
I said we're all out, okay?

966
00:54:40,614 --> 00:54:42,716
Okay. Jeez.

967
00:54:44,201 --> 00:54:45,636
(EXHALES)

968
00:54:49,373 --> 00:54:50,891
(FIREWORKS EXPLODING)

969
00:55:01,886 --> 00:55:02,987
(DOOR OPENS)

970
00:55:04,513 --> 00:55:06,782
HUGH: David, you're up early.

971
00:55:07,224 --> 00:55:08,558
Uh...

972
00:55:08,559 --> 00:55:09,726
Good morning.

973
00:55:09,727 --> 00:55:11,662
Yeah. Yeah, it is, isn't it?

974
00:55:12,772 --> 00:55:15,398
Listen, I was thinking about taking
the boat out for a little spin.

975
00:55:15,399 --> 00:55:17,168
Ah, I'm just gonna get some coffee.

976
00:55:17,360 --> 00:55:18,627
I'll make you one to go.

977
00:55:19,779 --> 00:55:21,130
I'm gonna wait for Jade.

978
00:55:21,655 --> 00:55:23,716
She's not gonna be up for hours.

979
00:55:23,908 --> 00:55:25,426
Gets that from her mother.

980
00:55:25,826 --> 00:55:27,678
Come on, it'll be fun.

981
00:55:28,287 --> 00:55:29,722
(ENGINE REVVING)

982
00:55:43,302 --> 00:55:44,820
(SIGHS)

983
00:55:46,472 --> 00:55:48,032
It's beautiful, isn't it?

984
00:55:48,224 --> 00:55:52,870
Yeah, we bought the place in
'96, and the kids were just...

986
00:55:54,397 --> 00:55:58,667
A little poison ivy, a few too many
mosquitoes, but I just love it.

987
00:56:00,111 --> 00:56:02,112
And you know, no matter what
was happening in our lives,

988
00:56:02,113 --> 00:56:06,008
we could come out here because
nothing would seem as bad.

989
00:56:08,119 --> 00:56:09,595
At least that was the idea.

990
00:56:11,330 --> 00:56:13,516
There's no need for any of this.

991
00:56:15,001 --> 00:56:17,460
You can just get to the point where
you ask me about last night.

992
00:56:17,461 --> 00:56:18,670
Last night?

993
00:56:18,671 --> 00:56:21,524
You and that woman you work with.

994
00:56:23,843 --> 00:56:25,343
I don't know what
you think you saw.

995
00:56:25,344 --> 00:56:26,821
I do.

996
00:56:27,471 --> 00:56:29,031
I know exactly what I saw.

997
00:56:29,724 --> 00:56:32,284
I'd be very careful, David.

998
00:56:35,604 --> 00:56:38,082
That's a serious accusation
you're about to make.

999
00:56:38,774 --> 00:56:42,128
If you think I'm gonna
tell Jade, I'm not.

1000
00:56:42,194 --> 00:56:43,737
If that's the reason why
you brought me out here.

1001
00:56:43,738 --> 00:56:45,113
But I'll tell you this.

1002
00:56:45,114 --> 00:56:48,551
If she found out,
it would kill her.

1003
00:56:48,617 --> 00:56:50,719
There's nothing to tell.

1004
00:56:52,163 --> 00:56:55,266
But if you continue down this
road, you will regret it.

1005
00:56:56,876 --> 00:56:58,477
You understand?

1006
00:57:07,303 --> 00:57:09,071
You've been quiet all day.

1007
00:57:09,263 --> 00:57:10,573
You okay?

1008
00:57:10,639 --> 00:57:14,535
Yeah. I'm all right.
I'm just tired.

1009
00:57:17,438 --> 00:57:19,790
Our dad's finally getting
to you, isn't he?

1010
00:57:21,817 --> 00:57:23,758
Does he compare you to
Chris, or is it just me?

1011
00:57:24,487 --> 00:57:27,364
It's all right. Your dad's
just having a hard time.

1012
00:57:27,365 --> 00:57:28,490
(CHUCKLES)

1013
00:57:28,491 --> 00:57:31,510
No, he's been having a
hard time for a while now.

1014
00:57:32,536 --> 00:57:34,597
He's an asshole.
He just can't hide it anymore.

1015
00:57:35,164 --> 00:57:37,600
"And Chris wouldn't even
know what a frat party was!

1016
00:57:38,042 --> 00:57:41,187
"Communications? Isn't
that for yoga instructors?

1017
00:57:41,962 --> 00:57:44,255
"Arizona State?
Why not major in alcoholism?

1018
00:57:44,256 --> 00:57:46,800
"I mean, Jesus Christ, Keith!

